P.append(passage("j8_observe_021", "The Patience of Stoplights", "红绿灯的耐心", 8,
    "一个红绿灯能告诉你很多关于一个城市节奏的信息。在我住的城市，主干道的红灯时长是九十秒，这在全国范围内属于偏长的。九十秒的等待在步行者的体感中被无限拉长——我观察过，大约有百分之三十五的行人会在红灯亮了六十秒之后开始张望，判断是否可以闯红灯。到了七十秒，又有百分之二十的人会迈出试探性的一步。而那些坚持等到绿灯的人，往往不是因为更有耐心，而是因为他们在看手机——注意力被转移了，时间的压迫感也随之减轻。最有趣的是凌晨时分的红绿灯。马路上空无一人一车，灯还在机械地变换着红黄绿。那个场景有一种超现实的荒诞感：一个为人类设计的系统，在没有人使用的时候仍然忠实地运转着。它不知道现在是凌晨三点，不知道路上没有人，不知道自己的存在在此刻毫无意义。但正是这种不知疲倦的机械忠诚，让我莫名地感到安慰——世界上至少有些东西是不会因为无人注目而停止工作的。",
    "Yī gè hónglǜdēng néng gàosu nǐ hěn duō guānyú yī gè chéngshì jiézòu de xìnxī.",
    "A traffic light can tell you a lot about a city's rhythm. In my city, main road red lights last ninety seconds—long by national standards. Ninety seconds stretches infinitely in a pedestrian's perception—I observed that about thirty-five percent of pedestrians start looking around after sixty seconds of red, judging whether to jaywalk. At seventy seconds, another twenty percent take a tentative step. Those who wait for green are often not more patient but distracted by phones—diverted attention lightens time's pressure. Most interesting are traffic lights at dawn. Streets empty of people and cars, lights still mechanically cycling red-yellow-green. The scene has a surreal absurdity: a system designed for humans, faithfully operating when no one uses it. It doesn't know it's three AM, doesn't know the road is empty, doesn't know its existence is momentarily meaningless. But this tireless mechanical loyalty somehow comforts me—at least some things in this world won't stop working just because nobody is watching.",
    mc("百分之三十五的行人在六十秒后开始张望，这说明了什么？", "What does 35% of pedestrians looking around after 60 seconds indicate?",
       [o("红灯时间设计不合理","hónglǜdēng shíjiān shèjì bù hélǐ","Traffic light timing is poorly designed"),
        o("人类对等待的忍耐力有一个普遍的阈值","rénlèi duì děngdài de rěnnàilì yǒu yī gè pǔbiàn de yùzhí","Human patience for waiting has a universal threshold",True),
        o("这个城市的交通很差","zhège chéngshì de jiāotōng hěn chà","This city's traffic is poor"),
        o("行人安全意识不强","xíngrén ānquán yìshi bù qiáng","Pedestrians lack safety awareness")], 0.45),
    mc("凌晨空无一人时红绿灯仍在运转的场景为什么让作者感到安慰？", "Why does the empty-street traffic light still cycling comfort the author?",
       [o("说明电力系统很可靠","shuōmíng diànlì xìtǒng hěn kěkào","Shows the power system is reliable"),
        o("不知疲倦的机械忠诚代表了一种不依赖人类注意力而持续运转的秩序","bù zhī píjuàn de jīxiè zhōngchéng dàibiǎo le yī zhǒng bù yīlài rénlèi zhùyìlì ér chíxù yùnzhuǎn de zhìxù","The tireless mechanical loyalty represents an order that persists without depending on human attention",True),
        o("红绿灯的灯光在夜里很好看","hónglǜdēng de dēngguāng zài yè lǐ hěn hǎokàn","Traffic lights look nice at night"),
        o("他害怕完全黑暗的街道","tā hàipà wánquán hēi'àn de jiēdào","He fears completely dark streets")], 0.5),
    mc("看手机的行人能等更久的原因是什么？", "Why can phone-checking pedestrians wait longer?",
       [o("手机上有倒计时","shǒujī shàng yǒu dàojìshí","Their phones have a countdown"),
        o("注意力被转移，减轻了等待的时间压迫感","zhùyìlì bèi zhuǎnyí, jiǎnqīng le děngdài de shíjiān yāpògǎn","Diverted attention lightens the sense of time pressure while waiting",True),
        o("他们不赶时间","tāmen bù gǎn shíjiān","They're not in a hurry"),
        o("手机让他们看不到红灯","shǒujī ràng tāmen kàn bú dào hónglǜdēng","Phones prevent them from seeing the red light")], 0.4)))

