P.append(passage("j8_observe_022", "The Handwriting of Strangers", "陌生人的笔迹", 8,
    "在共享办公空间的白板上，你能看到至少五种截然不同的笔迹共存于同一块书写面上。有一种字迹极小而工整，像是用直尺辅助写出来的——这通常属于做数据分析的人，他们连写字都追求精确。有一种字迹龙飞凤舞，潦草到几乎无法辨认——这往往是创意部门的产物，思维速度远超书写速度。有一种字迹总是使用大写字母和方框来强调重点——这是管理者的习惯，每一个字都透着一种「我在做决定」的气场。偶尔会出现一种特别柔和的圆体字迹，所有的拐角都被磨圆了——我后来发现这属于实习生，她们的书写方式还带着学生时代的影子。白板上这些笔迹的重叠和覆盖构成了一种独特的集体记忆。每周五下午清洁白板时，一周的讨论、争论和灵感就这样被一块湿抹布擦去了。我有时觉得这个动作本身就是一个隐喻：在这个时代，我们创造的大多数东西都是可擦除的。",
    "Zài gòngxiǎng bàngōng kōngjiān de báibǎn shàng, nǐ néng kàn dào zhìshǎo wǔ zhǒng jiérán bùtóng de bǐjì gòngcún yú tóngyī kuài shūxiě miàn shàng.",
    "On a shared office whiteboard, you can see at least five distinctly different handwriting styles coexisting on the same surface. One is tiny and precise, as if written with a ruler—typically from data analysts, who pursue accuracy even in writing. One is wildly cursive, nearly illegible—often from the creative department, thinking faster than writing speed allows. One always uses block capitals and boxes for emphasis—a manager's habit, every letter radiating 'I am making decisions.' Occasionally there's a particularly soft, rounded script with all corners smoothed—I discovered this belongs to interns, whose writing still carries the shadow of student days. These overlapping handwriting styles on the board form a unique collective memory. When the whiteboard is cleaned Friday afternoon, a week of discussions, debates, and inspirations are erased by a damp cloth. I sometimes think this act is itself a metaphor: in this era, most things we create are erasable.",
    mc("不同笔迹与职业角色之间的对应关系说明了什么？", "What does the correspondence between handwriting and professional roles illustrate?",
       [o("应该统一办公室的书写规范","yīnggāi tǒngyī bàngōngshì de shūxiě guīfàn","Office writing standards should be unified"),
        o("书写方式无意识地反映了一个人的思维模式和职业身份","shūxiě fāngshì wúyìshi de fǎnyìng le yī gè rén de sīwéi móshì hé zhíyè shēnfèn","Writing style unconsciously reflects a person's thinking pattern and professional identity",True),
        o("白板不适合办公使用","báibǎn bú shìhé bàngōng shǐyòng","Whiteboards aren't suitable for office use"),
        o("每个人的教育背景不同","měi gè rén de jiàoyù bèijǐng bùtóng","Everyone's educational background differs")], 0.45),
    mc("擦白板被比作隐喻，这个隐喻指什么？", "What does the whiteboard-erasing metaphor refer to?",
       [o("清洁工作很重要","qīngjié gōngzuò hěn zhòngyào","Cleaning is important"),
        o("这个时代我们创造的大多数内容都是临时的、可被轻易抹去的","zhège shídài wǒmen chuàngzào de dàduōshù nèiróng dōu shì línshí de, kě bèi qīngyì mǒ qù de","Most content we create in this era is temporary and easily erasable",True),
        o("每周应该更换白板","měi zhōu yīnggāi gēnghuàn báibǎn","Whiteboards should be replaced weekly"),
        o("讨论的结果应该被记录下来","tǎolùn de jiéguǒ yīnggāi bèi jìlù xiàlái","Discussion results should be recorded")], 0.5),
    mc("实习生的圆体字迹「带着学生时代的影子」暗示了什么？", "What does interns' rounded script 'carrying the shadow of student days' suggest?",
       [o("实习生字写得好看","shíxíshēng zì xiě de hǎokàn","Interns have pretty handwriting"),
        o("书写习惯保留了一个人的成长痕迹，职场尚未将其重塑","shūxiě xíguàn bǎoliú le yī gè rén de chéngzhǎng hénjì, zhíchǎng shàng wèi jiāng qí chóng sù","Writing habits preserve traces of one's growth, not yet reshaped by the workplace",True),
        o("学校应该教更多书写技巧","xuéxiào yīnggāi jiāo gèng duō shūxiě jìqiǎo","Schools should teach more writing skills"),
        o("实习生还不够专业","shíxíshēng hái búgòu zhuānyè","Interns aren't professional enough")], 0.45)))

P.append(passage("j8_urban_007", "The Social Contract of Dog Walking", "遛狗的社会契约", 8,
    "遛狗是城市社交中一种独特的破冰机制。两个素不相识的人在街上擦肩而过时绝不会主动搭话，但如果双方都牵着狗，一次对话几乎是不可避免的。对话的开端总是关于狗的：「它几岁了？」「是什么品种？」「好乖啊！」这些问题本身毫无信息价值，但它们的功能是建立一个安全的社交缓冲区——通过谈论狗来避免直接面对人与人之间的陌生感。更有趣的是，狗之间的互动往往主导着人之间的互动。如果两只狗互相嗅闻并友好地摇尾巴，主人们也会松弛下来，对话可能延伸到天气、小区设施甚至个人生活。但如果两只狗互相吠叫或对峙，主人们会迅速拉开距离，对话戛然而止。我观察到，有些人甚至会选择性地在特定时间遛狗，以便遇到那些狗与自己的狗「合得来」的邻居。这套由动物偏好驱动的社交过滤系统，比任何社交软件的算法都更诚实——它不考虑你的职业、收入或教育背景，只看你的狗是否愿意和对方的狗玩。",
    "Liú gǒu shì chéngshì shèjiāo zhōng yī zhǒng dútè de pò bīng jīzhì.",
    "Dog walking is a unique ice-breaking mechanism in urban social life. Two strangers passing on the street would never initiate conversation, but if both are walking dogs, dialogue is almost inevitable. It always starts about the dogs: 'How old?' 'What breed?' 'So well-behaved!' These questions have zero information value, but their function is to create a safe social buffer zone—talking about dogs to avoid directly facing interpersonal strangeness. More interesting, dogs' interactions often drive humans' interactions. If two dogs sniff each other and wag tails, owners relax and conversation may extend to weather, community facilities, even personal lives. But if dogs bark or posture at each other, owners quickly create distance and conversation halts. I've observed some people selectively walking dogs at specific times to encounter neighbors whose dogs 'get along' with theirs. This social filtering system driven by animal preferences is more honest than any social app algorithm—it doesn't consider your career, income, or education, only whether your dog is willing to play with theirs.",
    mc("遛狗时关于狗的寒暄本身有什么社交功能？", "What social function do dog-related pleasantries serve?",
       [o("获取关于狗的实用信息","huòqǔ guānyú gǒu de shíyòng xìnxī","Obtaining practical information about dogs"),
        o("建立安全的社交缓冲区，避免直接面对人际陌生感","jiànlì ānquán de shèjiāo huǎnchōng qū, bìmiǎn zhíjiē miànduì rénjì mòshēnggǎn","Creating a safe social buffer zone to avoid directly facing interpersonal strangeness",True),
        o("表达对动物的喜爱","biǎodá duì dòngwù de xǐ'ài","Expressing love for animals"),
        o("判断对方是否是好人","pànduàn duìfāng shìfǒu shì hǎo rén","Judging whether the other person is good")], 0.45),
    mc("作者说这套系统「比社交软件的算法更诚实」，原因是什么？", "Why does the author call this system 'more honest than social app algorithms'?",
       [o("狗不会说谎","gǒu bú huì shuōhuǎng","Dogs don't lie"),
        o("它只基于动物本能的直接反应来筛选社交对象，不涉及人类社会的身份标签","tā zhǐ jīyú dòngwù běnnéng de zhíjiē fǎnyìng lái shāixuǎn shèjiāo duìxiàng, bú shèjí rénlèi shèhuì de shēnfèn biāoqiān","It filters social contacts based only on animals' instinctive direct reactions, not human social identity labels",True),
        o("社交软件的算法不准确","shèjiāo ruǎnjiàn de suànfǎ bù zhǔnquè","Social app algorithms are inaccurate"),
        o("养狗的人都很友善","yǎng gǒu de rén dōu hěn yǒushàn","Dog owners are all friendly")], 0.5),
    mc("人们选择特定时间遛狗这一现象说明了什么？", "What does people choosing specific times for dog walking indicate?",
       [o("他们的作息时间很固定","tāmen de zuòxī shíjiān hěn gùdìng","They have fixed schedules"),
        o("人类会利用动物的社交偏好来间接选择自己的人际圈","rénlèi huì lìyòng dòngwù de shèjiāo piānhǎo lái jiānjiē xuǎnzé zìjǐ de rénjìquān","Humans use animals' social preferences to indirectly select their own social circles",True),
        o("不同品种的狗需要不同的遛狗时间","bùtóng pǐnzhǒng de gǒu xūyào bùtóng de liú gǒu shíjiān","Different dog breeds need different walking times"),
        o("为了避开交通高峰","wèile bìkāi jiāotōng gāofēng","To avoid traffic peaks")], 0.45)))

